Preheat your oven to 220 degrees. Peel and chop the @sweet potato{1} into small 2cm
chunks. Place on a lined #baking tray{} with a glug of @oil{} and a pinch of @salt{},
pop on the top shelf of your #oven{} for ~{20-25%minutes} until slightly crispy.

> If you remove them from the oven and they aren't quite cooked, just pop them back
> in for 5 mins more.

Cut the @onion{1} in half through the root, peel and chop into roughly 1cm pieces.
Remove the core from the @yellow pepper{1} and chop into 2cm pieces. Finely chop
the @coriander{1} stalks and roughly chop the leaves (keep them separate). Peel and
grate the @garlic cloves{2} (or use a #garlic press{} if you have one). Cut the
@green chilli{1/2} in half lengthways and remove the seeds, then finely chop. Empty
the @black beans{1} into a #sieve{} or #colander{} and rinse under cold water.

Put your onion in a large #frying pan{} on medium heat with a drizzle of @oil{} and
cook for ~{5%minutes} (if it gets a bit brown, don't worry, it will just add to the
flavour). Next, add your pepper and cook for another ~{5%minutes}. Then add the
coriander stalks, garlic and chilli (add less if you're not a huge fan of spice!).
Throw in the @ground cumin{1/2%tsp} and @smoked paprika{1/2%tsp}, stir everything
together and cook for ~{1%minute} before adding your black beans, @vegetable stock
pot{1} and @water{400}. Bring to a simmer and gently bubble away for
~{10-15%minutes} until your veijoada has reduced by half.

While your veijoada is cooking, grate the @mature cheddar cheese{30} and keep to the
side. Chop the @vine tomatoes{2} into small 1cm pieces. Cut the @echalion shallot{1}
in half through the root, peel and then finely chop into ½cm pieces (if you can!).
Cut the @baby gem lettuce{1} in half lengthways, remove the root, then slice into
roughly 1cm wide slices.

Grate the @lime{1} zest into a large #bowl{}, squeeze in the lime juice and add your
shallot. Add a drizzle of @oil{}, a pinch of @salt{}, a good grind of @black pepper{}
and a pinch of @sugar{} (if you have some). Mix together with a #fork{} then add
in your tomato and baby gem lettuce. Leave to the side.

Spoon your cooked veijoada into an #ovenproof dish{}, then remove your sweet potato
from your oven. Preheat your #grill{} to high. Arrange your sweet potato on top of
your veijoada and sprinkle over your cheese. Pop under your grill for
~{3-5%minutes} until your cheese has melted.

Serve your veijoada bake in #bowls{} with your salad on the side and your coriander
leaves sprinkled over the top. Enjoy!